Mauritius to Spend 21.5 Billion Rupees on Roads Until 2013, Le Defi Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-06-30T05:49:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/mauritius-to-spend-21-5-billion-rupees-on-roads-until-2013-le-defi-says.html
Mauritius will invest 21.5 billion
rupees ($756 million) on road infrastructure from 2011 to 2013,
Le Defi Quotidien reported, citing Prime Minister Navinchandra Ramgoolam.  The number of vehicles in the country has increased 57
percent to about 400,000 in 2011 compared with 2001, the Port
Louis-based newspaper cited Ramgoolam.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at
   kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
